        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>5 Sepr 1865</date>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I send you<lb/> a paper called the Christian Advocate<lb/>
                containing some remarks on the<lb/> late dedication of a “progressive<lb/> Jewish
                Temple” in this city. Should<lb/> you deem those reflections worthy<lb/> of any
                notice in your publication I<lb/> have to request that you will not<lb/> in any way
                intimate that you recd<lb/> the paper from a correspondent or<lb/> any thing of that
                kind, because it<lb/> is considered here now a <sic>henious</sic> of<lb/>fence to do
                aught which may in any<lb/> way reflect on Reform or Reformers,<lb/> and as I am
                marked, I do not desire<lb/> to be publicly mixed with their</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>affair—Hashictures<add>?</add> are how<lb/>=ever correct &amp; true to the letter,
                the<lb/> denial by both the Revd professors<lb/> of all that we have been
                taught<lb/> as constituting Judaism, was com<lb/>plete &amp;
                emphatic—Rationalism<lb/> is to govern, against the words of<lb/>
                inspiration—Miracles such as<lb/> the <placeName>red sea</placeName> dividing to
                permit the cross<lb/>ing of <placeName>Judeas</placeName>
                <add>?</add>, are also mere follies,<lb/> restoration to
                    <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> &amp; the coming<lb/> of a redeemer to
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> only old fogy<lb/> notions—and all the landmarks
                of<lb/> our faith entirely gone—and not<lb/> to side with these tenets is to<lb/> be
                ostracised: for <hi rend="underline">all</hi> the people<lb/> are led away nearly by
                heresies<lb/> of the day. I wish you all the<lb/> complements of the season that
                you<lb/> may be inscribed in the book of life<lb/> &amp; that the coming year may be
                a<lb/> year of joy &amp; happiness to you &amp; that<lb/> your labors in the
                vineyard<lb/> may bring forth abundant &amp; good fruits—I <del>wish</del> send<lb/>
                $10 herein as I know I must be in<lb/>debted to you I do not wish you<lb/> to
                acknowledge receipt in your<lb/> paper as I shall then be pointed<lb/> out &amp; I
                candidly tell you that<lb/> for policy sake I am compelled to<lb/> be at least or
                seem passive, tho'<lb/> I never disguise my disgust &amp; abhor<lb/>=ence of the
                schemes of those who<lb/> call themselves here teachers in<lb/>
                <placeName>Israel</placeName>— With regards I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">truly yrs</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Abraham Esq</persName>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
        </body>
